That strategy is also helpful to employers and individuals in comparing qualifications across the Union and across diverse education and training systems.
I am sure that this key initiative is helping people in Europe to face the challenges and reap the benefits of a knowledge-based society.
We are looking forward not only to further discussions but also to further cooperation following the recent adoption of the proposal.
Â Â  â MrÂ President, ladies and gentlemen, the Lisbon Strategy proposes to speed up the process of modernising the European education and training systems, with the aim of making the European economy the most competitive economy in the world by 2010.
